<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900411-0048</DOCNO><DOCID>900411-0048.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- CAE Industries Ltd.:   Link Flight Unit Awarded   U.S. Air Force, Army Jobs</HL><DATE>04/11/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   T.CAE</CO><GV>DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF)</GV><LP>   CAE Industries Ltd. said its Link Flight Simulationdivision, of Binghamton, N.Y., was awarded two contracts thattotal 51 million Canadian dollars (US$43.9 million) to modifyflight simulators for the U.S. Air Force and Army.   CAE, an electronic and aviation equipment maker, said aC$32.7 million contract involves modifying and upgradingthree F16 flight simulators, which it built for the U.S. AirForce. That project, which includes equipment designed andbuilt at its Houston plant, is scheduled for completion in1993. A C$18.3 million contract is for the updating of nineApache helicopter combat-mission simulators made by thecompany for the U.S. Army. Those modification kits will bedeveloped in Binghamton. Work is scheduled to be completed inFebruary 1992.</LP><TEXT>   CAE purchased Singer Co.'s Link Domestic Simulation andamp;Training System division in 1988 for US$560 million.</TEXT></DOC>